r\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 In a recent report entitled "Leadership 2030," management consultants Hay Group identified six emerging "megatrends" that, they say, are set to shape the new world order over the next 20 years: globalization 2.0, climate change, demographic shifts, individualization, digital lifestyle and work, and technology convergence.\par \par \uc2 Georg Vielmetter , Hay Group's head of Leadership and Talent Practice, Europe, sets out some ways in which leaders can become advocates and agents of change, mastering the techniques and tools needed for survival.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Step off your pedestal\u8212\'20\'14there are no more heroes.\par \par \uc2 The days of one or two "heroic" leaders determining organizational strategy from on high are well and truly over. With globalization progressing at speed and a comprehensive shift of power toward the East\u8212\'20\'14compounded by the European sovereign debt crisis\u8212\'20\'14international competition will grow fiercer and markets even more diverse.\par \par \uc2 In this \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it's "survival of the agile," as leaders strive to demonstrate strategic thinking, cognitive skills and the ability to adapt to new authority structures.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 CSR climbs the boardroom agenda\par \par \uc2 As climate change accelerates, organizations and leaders will be asked to take greater environmental accountability, embedding the "green" agenda into business operations.\par \par \uc2 Balancing issues of compliance, finance and \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  will demand a higher degree of strategic and conceptual thought from leaders. But their key responsibility will be to act as advocates of change within the organization, leading by example to adopt eco-friendly solutions.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 World-wide talent "brain cycle" brings staff loyalty into sharp focus\par \par \uc2 As life expectancy in the developed world rises and populations stagnate, populations in the developing nations are booming\u8212\'20\'14creating significant demographic imbalances. As a result, many countries will suffer skills shortages as highly educated migrants return home and use their new skills to promote local development.\par \par \uc2 This "brain cycle" will intensify the fight for talent and staff retention will be absolutely essential to business sustainability and success. Leaders in the developed world must prioritize staff loyalty\u8212\'20\'14engendering a sense of belonging and purpose among an increasingly diverse work force\u8212\'20\'14to shore up the future of their organization.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Self-fulfillment moves the masses\par \par \uc2 For the new, highly educated work force, traditional motivating factors such as pay will be taken for granted. Instead, as the notion of a "career" shifts and individuals create joint personal and professional goals, recognition, self-development, self-direction, values-driven engagement and work-life balance become more important.\par \par \uc2 Leaders must therefore be supportive, skilfully and interchangeably adopting the roles of boss, mediator and coach, to encourage autonomy and secure commitment to organizational objectives.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The digital revolution is a blessing and a curse for the 2030 leader\par \par \uc2 Constantly connected to the Internet via smart phones and tablets, employees are now always "switched on," and the lines between work and personal lives blur. And, as digital tools offer inexpensive, easy and fast communication, cooperation and organization, workplaces are no longer tied to bricks and mortar.\par \par \uc2 To combat the threat of remote working to engagement and culture, leaders must learn to lead from afar, using effective virtual and face-to-face communication.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Back to the books\u8212\'20\'14innovations in science call for technical prowess\par \par \uc2 Over the next two decades, the trends toward miniaturization and virtualization will drive the convergence between nano, bio and information technologies and cognitive sciences, or NBIC.\par \par \uc2 Many of the NBIC technologies market-ready today would have sounded like science fiction until very recently: neuro-pharmaceuticals, modified enzymes, medical implants and neuro-implants, to name but a few.\par \par \uc2 Successful forays into NBIC technology require leaders to act as intermediaries and visionaries: to recognize and evaluate technology potential, forge cooperation and inspire all those involved to stay focused on the main goal.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 It's not organizational apocalypse, it's business as usual\par \par \uc2 To flourish in the brave new world of business, leaders must address the inevitable ripples of change brought about by these megatrends. They are already making their mark, and are here to stay.\par \par \uc2 By getting to grips with different ways of working, honing new skills and prioritizing collaboration, loyalty and effective communication, leaders can help their organizations' transition. As the practices, behavior and values of the "new" work force become business as usual, the post-heroic leader will come out on top.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 iacc : \uc2 Accounting/Consulting\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c41 : \uc2 Management Issues | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpin : \uc2 FC&E Industry News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 usa : \uc2 United States | namz : \uc2 North America\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha