spnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 From Mr Michael Littlechild.\par \par \uc2 Sir, Gillian Tett ("When making shampoo becomes a service to society", February 4) steers a sensible line in her remarks about the role of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  in salving the corporate conscience.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 I am more sceptical, however, about her premise that what we are witnessing is the relentless rise of CSR. It is true that few people hold any more to Milton Friedman's belief that the only social responsibility of business is to make money - at least not publicly. But I don't think either that the overriding concern of business should be to worry about wider social challenges.\par \par \uc2 Businesses should be held responsible primarily for their products and the way they make them. Conscience-stricken consumers do not want their shampoo to harm either the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  or their health. They also care that the manufacturer and its suppliers don't pay bribes, have paid decent living wages to employees who work in safe conditions and have not polluted rivers (even if the government of the country doesn't care).\par \par \uc2 For me this adds up to good business ethics rather than social responsibility. Consumers are no longer fooled by a philanthropic smokescreen which masks some of the more dirty tricks of business. What we are witnessing is the rise of business ethics rather than the growing strategic importance of CSR.\par \par \uc2 Michael Littlechild, Director, GoodCorporation, London SW6, UK\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpex : \uc2 FC&E Executive News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PUB\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 The Financial Times Limited (AAIW/EIW)\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b AN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Document FTCOM00020120208e828000jh\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpad