num\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Construction\par \par \uc2 There are plenty of ways you can make a difference, writes Hesham Zakai\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Tony Hackney is not your typical entrepreneur. He deals in timber, not technology, and, far from being a budding start-up, presides over a company with a history that streches back 164 years.\par \par \uc2 "I was privileged to be a nominee, but then I felt like a bit of an imposter," he says. But being an entrepreneur isn't all about zeitgeist projects, flash suits and tech graduates.\par \par \uc2 "I think the word can be misused sometimes. Being an entrepreneur is also about making a difference where you are."\par \par \uc2 Mr Hackney has certainly done that. The 53-year-old took over Berwickshire-based \uc2 BSW Timber\uc2 , the largest sawmilling business in the UK, in 2008 when the company was making a significant loss. Four years and 60 per cent growth later, BSW has a turnover of \u163\'00\'A3163m and posted profits of nearly \u163\'00\'A320m last year.\par \par \uc2 The company's transformation is all the more impressive given the difficult market conditions, but as a seasoned manager, Mr Hackney was determined not to let that sway his decisions.\par \par \uc2 "If you focus too much on the market forum and not what you can change, you get nowhere," he says. It's an empowering attitude that must be present at the top of a company and reach through to its employees, "leadership is a massive part of being an entrepreneur".\par \par \uc2 His career path has been bumpy, to say the least. Mr Hackney joined the \uc2 National Coal Board\uc2  straight out of school, and by the time of the miners' strike in the 1980s, he was a senior manager.\par \par \uc2 "It was a very difficult experience. Although I had risen to senior manager, I'd grown up with the guys on the coalface and had to respect their position to go on strike," he recalls.\par \par \uc2 But for Mr Hackney, management meant making tough decisions and sticking to responsibilities.\par \par \uc2 "I had to go back to work," he says definitively. The experience did not affect his relationship with his staff; he still remains friends with many of them, he adds.\par \par \uc2 At BSW, Mr Hackney has worked hard to modernise a traditional industry and reform the way homegrown timber is seen in the UK.\par \par \uc2 "It was perceived as inferior [to international equivalents] but by raising new technical solutions to problems we've tried to raise the bar," he says. The old association of construction with bricks and mortar must be supplanted with a genuine consideration of timber, which can be incredibly durable and has a positive effect on the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  if used properly, he explains.\par \par \uc2 "A lot of people talk about renewable resources, green projects and their \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  nowadays. Well, if you are serious about it, use timber."\par \par \uc2 Despite the modernisation drive, BSW has retained its roots, including its headquarters in the small, leafy town of Earlston in Berwickshire. It has six sawmills in the UK and one in Latvia, employing more than 900 people and having the capacity to produce around 1m cubic metres of sawn timber a year.\par \par \uc2 Mr Hackney attributes his success as an entrepreneur to a "real passion for new ideas and determination to bookmark a trend".\par \par \uc2 But he is keen to stress that one entrepreneur does not make a company. "There's a real underestimation of the ingenuity of a workforce," he says. "There are brilliant people everywhere who pick up and pass things on."\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 borbif : \uc2 BSW Timber PLC\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i1 : \uc2 Energy | i16 : \uc2 Electricity/Gas Utilities | i16101 : \uc2 Electric Power Generation | i163 : \uc2 Electric Power Generation - Alternative Energy | ieutil : \uc2 Electric Utilities\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PUB\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 The Financial Times Limited (AAIW/EIW)\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15