\li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PG\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 06\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 2013 The Financial Times Ltd. All rights reserved. Please do not cut and paste FT articles and redistribute by email or post to the web.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 It is not what you know but who you know, goes the old saying. The truth of the adage is borne out by the support that recent MBA graduates have given each other since leaving the classroom.\par \par \uc2 In a survey of 1,390 MBA graduates from the class of 2009, almost half (47 per cent) reported having received a job offer through their MBA alumni network since completing their studies. Nearly one-third (32 per cent) of poll respondents have themselves employed someone as a result of contacts made through their alumni network, and three-quarters expect their connections to open doors for them in the future.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The strength of MBA alumni groups - which were cited by 51 per cent of graduates as the most important network to their career prospects - is illustrated by continued communication between peers.\par \par \uc2 Of those polled, 72 per cent reported regular contact with their fellow students three years after graduation.\par \par \uc2 The importance of networking was not lost on graduates even when they were choosing business schools. Three-quarters (76 per cent) told the FT that networking was an important factor in their decision to study for a full-time MBA. For the majority (52 per cent), networking played a signi\u64257\'FB\'01- cant part in determining which schools they applied to. Among alumni of the top 10 schools of 2013, this \u64257\'FB\'01gure was 66 per cent.\par \par \uc2 - AdamPalin Despite talk of a shift to distance learning, it seems there is no substitute for bricks and mortar, with business schools keen to create dramatic new architecture. Fudan University School ofManagementis a prime example, with plans for a new Shanghai campus (below) For a slideshowofrecent and planned projects, go to{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.ft.com/business-education/mba2013"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.ft.com/business-education/mba2013}}}\uc2  \u10132\'27\'94Talent scheme extends graduates' UKstay British business schools argue that students have been put off studying for an MBA in the UK in recent years by a tightening of immigration rules that limit their stay after they graduate.\par \par \uc2 Now the UKgovernment has announced that fromApril 2013 it will add a further 1,000 places to its Exceptional Talent scheme, specifically for MBA graduates to stay in Britain to start their own businesses.\par \par \uc2 The scheme will double in size fromthe current 1,000 work visas for graduates from various disciplines, including MBA alumni.\par \par \uc2 "We have always been clear that we want Britain to attract the brightest and best talent fromaround the world," says Theresa May, the home secretary. - Charlotte Clarke Finding cold, hard facts about climate change C hina, India and Brazil have been the trendy destinations for MBA study trips - until now.\par \par \uc2 In December a group of students from Stanford Graduate School of Business made Antarctica their destination of choice.\par \par \uc2 So novel was the idea that Stanford dean Garth Saloner decided to go too.\par \par \uc2 The aim of the trip was to investigate climate change and business issues around it, in an \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  that is being affected more than most. David Shackelton, a distant relative of Ernest Shackleton, the Antarctic explorer, was one of the student organisers of the trip and brought together speakers from industry and policy as well as climate activists to talk on the subject.\par \par \uc2 What the trip brought home most forcibly to him was that climate change is often dif\u64257\'FB\'01cult to take seriously because it cannot be seen on a day-to-day basis. "It is still very intangible," he says.\par \par \uc2 For Shackelton, one of the most compelling issues is that companies have to act. "A lot of these problems can be solved pro\u64257\'FB\'01tably. You can call it \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but it also makes economic sense." The students and the dean were blown away by their visit. "There, you really are out in nature. There are no people. There is no litter. The path [you follow] has been made by penguins, not by people," says Prof Saloner. - Della Bradshaw Report: study trips, page 55.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PUB\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 The Financial Times Limited (AAIW/EIW)\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b AN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Document FTFT000020130128e91s0002z\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {