icles and redistribute by email or post to the web.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Organisations do not exist in isolation. Their "stakeholders" include local residents, politicians and, of course, employees. Embedding a sense of the purpose of the organisation, its values and its role in the community can mean as much to staff retention as a generous benefits package.\par \par \uc2 Ruth Colling of Nicholson McBride business psychologists recalls teaching schoolchildren while at Warburg Bank: "\b \highlight22\uc2 Corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  has existed for years. If you work for a company where your values are mirrored in your work, then the sense of 'fit' is better. You understand your role and your sense of purpose.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 "This sense defines the culture and vision of the organisation and this is cascaded down so people understand the competencies and behaviours needed to deliver that vision."\par \par \uc2 Ben Willmott, head of public policy at the \uc2 Chartered Institute of Personnel and Development\uc2 , emphasises the importance of companies having a strategic narrative that everybody can understand: "The issue of culture and values has never had a higher profile as a result of the breakdown in trust in the City, as well as scandals like phone hacking and concerns over the \uc2 National Health Service\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "Of course, values are only worth more than a passing reference on the company intranet if they actually influence how people behave. Senior leaders need to hold a mirror up to their own behaviour and consider its impact in setting the overarching culture."\par \par \uc2 CSR programmes include enabling employees to become school governors and reciprocal arrangements between sectors.\par \par \uc2 Barry Cooke of Make Architects adds that, at interview, architects are attracted by Make's aim of preserving and enhancing the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  as far as possible.\par \par \uc2 Jane Wood, \uc2 Dimension Data\uc2 's European HR head, says executives value such opportunities: "We staged a leadership event for 80 leaders in Munich which involved building bikes for a local orphanage."\par \par \uc2 According to \uc2 Lynne Weedall\uc2 , group HR and strategy director at Carphone Warehouse: "When engaging with employees we stress the 'why?'. Our mission is to make more people's lives better through connected technology.\par \par \uc2 "Different teams devise bespoke activities which fit this vision. One team chose to run sessions for older people on how best to use technology. We ask employees to be clear about our purpose and challenge them to bring it to life.\par \par \uc2 "We brought 1,200 managers together via a live satellite challenge and they transformed a local library into a community 'hub'."\par \par \uc2 The impact of such community involvement can be measured. Brewer \uc2 SABMiller\uc2  sees its businesses as part of the local communities in which it operates. It commissioned research by Professor Ethan Kapstein of Insead Business School that showed that for every person it employs in Uganda, the company's presence supports a further 200 jobs or more in the wider economy.\par \par \uc2 The company's "Ten Priorities, One Future" programme defines the environmental, social and economic issues that are most material to its business. Andy Wales, senior vice-president for sustainable development, says: "Our activity is more than local philanthropy. It needs to be aligned to the core business strategy.\par \par \uc2 "One example is in Colombia, where our local business runs the entrepreneurship programme 'Destapa Futuro', and employees mentor the beneficiaries of the programme.\par \par \uc2 "In 2011 we measured employee perception among 400 UK staff and found 95 per cent of respondents agreed the company is serious about its responsibility in society."\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ciprv : \uc2 Chartered Institute of Personnel and Development\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | eecz : \uc2 European Union Countries | eurz : \uc2 Europe | weurz : \uc